BFN 

  [Text] Trade between Bangladesh and Myanmar [Burma] will 
start soon after signing the border trade agreement between the 
two countries. The visiting Myanmar minister for trade, 
Lieutenant General Tun Kyi, said this on his arrival in Dhaka 
today from Chittagong. Talking to newsmen, he said the 
agreement will be signed on Wednesday. The Myanmar trade 
minister and his Bangladesh counterpart, Shamsul Islam, will 
sign it. The Myanmar minister said border trade can help 
(?accelerate) the development of the regions of the two 
countries across their borders. 
  Replying to a question, Mr. Kyi said his government welcomed 
the Myanmar refugees back home. 

